{"page":1,"results":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":80170,"known_for_department":"Directing","name":"Tadeusz Chmielewski","original_name":"Tadeusz Chmielewski","popularity":0.0618,"profile_path":"/uBjTd6bVeg9xuzkaSFbsyo8Q6F4.jpg","known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/6iwrNSyEu6sgfEXAXWnWrWpNVwI.jpg","id":16238,"title":"How I Unleashed World War II, Part II: Following the Arms","original_title":"Jak rozpętałem drugą wojnę światową: Cz. 2 - Za bronią","overview":"After escaping across Europe from Stalag camp, Dolas's ride to Cyprus is stopped when his ship in sunk by an Italian submarine. Although he and some of his fellow sailors are rescued by an Allied ship, they find themselves conscripted into the French Foreign Legion in Beirut, Dolas becoming a cook.","poster_path":"/wefaG7zZ5ivfGkDSwk1r9rqPwJ3.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"pl","genre_ids":[35,12,10752],"popularity":0.3547,"release_date":"1970-04-06","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":7.6,"vote_count":76},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/gujTminHou8yfdVhJxn4wiGuTpR.jpg","id":75011,"title":"How I Unleashed World War II, Part I: The Escape","original_title":"Jak rozpętałem drugą wojnę światową: Cz. 1 - Ucieczka","overview":"On the night of August 31, 1939, Dolas, from a platoon reinforcing a train station on the German border, falls asleep in a train car and unknowingly crosses into Germany. The moment he shoots a German, who he thinks is a saboteur, the German invasion of Poland begins, and Dolas is convinced it was his fault. He is taken to Stalag POW camp, the first destination in his odyssey around Europe.","poster_path":"/2smM51Pz6Bt2jjabd7UPyVkM4wu.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"pl","genre_ids":[35,10752,12],"popularity":1.2439,"release_date":"1970-04-02","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":7.606,"vote_count":66},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/mM44QD0H7SYilFixKvfu5S5fQ1Y.jpg","id":64115,"title":"I Hate Mondays","original_title":"Nie lubię ponie